			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">An untrusted crash dumping facility was added in issue 2595.  So far, it just writes a dump to a file (if the sandbox is turned off) or to stdout.  We should extend it with the ability to upload a dump via HTTP/HTTPS to a server, when running in the browser.

One tricky aspect is: What interface do we use for uploading?  Can we rely on the PPAPI proxy to function if we've just crashed?  This might not work if the PPAPI proxy crashed, or if its data structures were corrupted.  Also, the threading model might be too restrictive to upload in the context of a crash.
